Reasoning: The paper uses image recognition techniques to study food perception on Instagram, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. It also analyzes the relationship between the perception gap and health outcomes, which could be considered a social impact (cs.SI) aspect. The paper also uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the captions of the food images, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Additionally, the study involves human subjects and their perceptions, which could be considered a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect. Finally, the paper deals with a large dataset of images, which could be considered a multimedia (cs.MM) aspect.
